title.narrative: Tamil Nadu Empowerment and Poverty Reduction

description.narrative: The project development objective would be to empower the poor and improve livelihoods through: (a) developing and strengthening pro-poor local institutions/groups (including Village Panchayats); (b) building skills and capacities of the poor; and (c) financing productive demand-driven sub-project investments.

title.narrative: At least 15 partnerships established across at least five sectors with public/private sector organizations and communities

target.value: At least 15 partnerships across five or more sectors

title.narrative: At least 70% of Process monitoring recommendations agreed with the management are reviewed and implemented/action taken.
75% of CPs in existing districts and 50% of CPs new districts are enrolled in centers and regularly offering services.
COM is revisited annually incorporating recommendations of process monitoring and other field experience and community feedback
Annual staff performance appraisal conducted (PFT, Districts, State) and staff rewarded accordingly.
GAAP reviewed once in a year and recommendations implemented.
Grievances related to delivery of project benefits that are addressed-(number)
Grievances registered related to delivery of project benefits addressed (%)
At least 40% of village institutions (VPRC and PLF) have federated and are benefitting through access to financial linkages or through delivery of services (PVP and other program)
At least 100,000 members of target HHs placed in jobs through project facilitation (for both existing and additional project districts)
At least 30% of the total VPs have accessed incentive fund as per the agreed guidelines.
At least 50% of CP centers (Magamai/SLIF) are able to meet all the operational cost on their own after year 2.
At least 70% of CBOs (VPRCs and PLFs) are graded as A or B
60% of CLFs are making profits after 2 years of commencement of business.
At least 50% of eligible target youth, have receive skills enhancement and have been linked to employment/self-employment.
At least 60% of VPs have at least 5 CPs identified, trained and offering services.

At least 85% of the target HHs have accessed funds through Project, linkage with banks or other financial resources or have benefitted through income generating activities or through social safety net
At least 70% of differently abled, Vulnerable and Tribals have accessed funds from the project and other sources and have started livelihood activities or employment
80% of target HHs mobilized into CBOs (Percentage, Custom)
At least 70% of the identified vulnerable populations e.g. disabled and tribal are organized into SHGs

baseline.value: 4% of HHs with differently abled and 6% of STs organized into SHGs

title.narrative: At least 80% of the CBOs (VPRCs, EAGs, VPs and Federations) have accessed and managed project funds according to rules and procedures

target.value: At least 80% of the CBOs (VPRCs, EAGs, VPs and Federations) have accessed and managed project funds according to rules andprocedures

actual.value: 100% of VPRCs have received the 1st installment of funds; 99% have received the 2nd installment and 78% received the 3rd installment

title.narrative: At least 50% of the SHGs of the poor have received multiple dose of credit (two or more bank linkages) directly from the bank or through the PLF bulk loan.

actual.value: 89.7% of the SHGs received multiple dose of credit. (Phase-I-95% & Phase -II 84.5%)

title.narrative: Empowerment, measured through women's ability to influence decisions and household participation in Gram Sabha meetings, increased by at least 10%

actual.value: Intra-household decision making 9% higher on purchase of household durables, 21% on choice of livelihood activity and 31% on GramSabha meeting participation

title.narrative: Economic well-being of target households - measured as a reduction in high cost loans, increase in livelihood assets and proportionof skilled laborers - improved by at least 20%

baseline.value: Data available for economic well-being indicator

target.value: At least 20% increase in key indicators of economic well-being

actual.value: Number of high cost loans reduced by 29% and proportion of skilled laborers within household more than 30% higher

title.narrative: At least 70% of VPRCs and EAGs receive support for livelihood plans in accordance with agreed service standards conducted through Report Card

target.value: at least 70% of VPRCs and EAGs have received support

title.narrative: In at least in 90% of CBOs, poor/ ultra poor women are occupying decision making positions in VPRC and PLFs

actual.value: 98% of CBOs poor/ultra poor women are occupying decision making position in VPRC and PLFs.

title.narrative: At least 20% increase in incremental income against base year for 50% of the target households by end of project (EOP)

baseline.value: mean annual income of target HHs (ultra poor and poor) = RS 7800 to 9,500 at constant 1993-94 prices

target.value: At least 20% increase in incremental income against base year for 50% of the target households by end of project (EOP).

actual.value: Income gain observed in 71.3% of the households at the MTR
